                <note rend="inline" type="source">691.003/31: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-22T14:00:00+03:25">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1928—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 22—10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. My 28, March 20, noon, point (4). A bill consisting of one article was
                    presented the night of March 18 by the Minister of Finance to the Medjliss as
                        follows:<note n="21" xml:id="d597fn21">Quotation not paraphrased.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The National Consultative Assembly approves of the attached customs
                            tariff and authorizes the Government to negotiate special customs
                            treaties, within the maximum and minimum limits of the tariff, with
                            foreign governments. The life of such treaties shall not be more than
                            five years.</p>
                        <p>“<hi rend="smallcaps">Note</hi>: The maximum customs tariff limit will be
                            levied on the merchandise of governments which make customs treaties
                            after May 11.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
